# Implement Right-Side Drawer for Mission Control

## Goal Description
The goal is to replace the existing modal windows for identifying "Add New Project" and "Upload SBOM Report" in the Mission Control section with right-side drawer components. This will provide a more modern and consistent user experience, aligning with the "Mission Control" aesthetic.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> This change mainly affects the UI/UX of the "Add New Project" and "Upload SBOM" flows. No backend changes are expected.

## Proposed Changes

### Client
#### [MODIFY] [scan/page.tsx](file:///C:/Users/Aditya/SCOUT_Frontend/client/src/pages/scoutCustomPages/scan/page.tsx)
-   Replace the `Dialog` component controlling `isModalOpen` (Add New Project) with a `Sheet` component.
    -   Set `side="right"` for the `SheetContent`.
    -   Ensure `SheetContent` has appropriate width and styling (e.g., `sm:max-w-[600px]`).
    -   Migrate the existing content (stepper, input fields, connector selection) into the `SheetContent`.
-   Replace the `Dialog` component controlling `showUploadModal` (Upload SBOM/Archive) with a `Sheet` component.
    -   Set `side="right"` for the `SheetContent`.
    -   Migrate the [UploadModal](file:///C:/Users/Aditya/SCOUT_Frontend/client/src/pages/scoutCustomPages/scan/page.tsx#3807-4023) component logic to use `Sheet`.
-   Ensure all state handlers (opening/closing) work correctly with the new `Sheet` components.

